frameDefinitions: A Cognizer computes a Result on the basis of input Numbers by addition.
The absolute Value of a quantifiable Attribute  of an item is determined by adding up the values for the Attribute of the individuals or parts that make up the item.
This frame contains transparent nouns (and some adjectives) denoting quantities of a Mass or of Individuals.

This frame models the semantic contribution of negation, in which the profiled content of the Negated_proposition is asserted to contrast incompatibly with a corresponding Factual_situation, which is normally implicit.
In this frame an Ingestor takes a Substance into his or her body.
A Part is considered to be a member of the set described by the Total.
frameExamples: Defence is provided in West Germany by armed forces whose number <t>totals</t> close to half a million men and women
He found them in the <t>deluge</t> of papers on his desk.
You should refrain from <t>taking</t> vodka up the nose.
Dr. Nelson <t>numbers</t> among the world?s foremost geotechnical engineering experts.
listRoleDefinitions: The person doing the calculation.
The <fen>Numbers</fen> that are used in the calculation.
The outcome of the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s calculcations.
The time at which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> operates on the <fen>Numbers</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Cognizer</fen> performs their calculation
The value of an attribute.
The scalar property of a concrete or abstract entity.
A set of numbers that add up to the <fen>Value</fen>.
The <fen>Quantity</fen>-denoting <t>Target</t> word.
A substance that is being quantified.
A collection of entities.
The situation which is presented as false overall. The particular focus of negation which contrasts with the <fen>Factual_situation</fen> is not separately marked.

The situation or part of situation that actually pertains, in contradistinction to the profiled situation in the <fen>Negated_proposition</fen> that is asserted not to pertain.  In spoken language and casual written language, but not in normatively edited written texts, the <fen>Factual_situation</fen> may be expressed as an unmarked clause immediately preceding or following the <fen>Negated_proposition</fen>.
The <fen>Delivery_device</fen> is the means by which the <fen>Substance</fen> is ingested.
The <fen>Ingestor</fen> ingests the <fen>Substance</fen>.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the drug or other substance that is ingested by the <fen>Ingestor</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Ingestor</fen> ingests the <fen>Substance</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Ingestor</fen> ingests the <fen>Substance</fen>.
The complex multi-part entity of which a constituent <fen>Part</fen> is specified.
A subset of the <fen>Total</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the subset relation holds.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the subset relation holds.
listRoleExamples: During the first three years of drug squad work, <fex>arrests</fex> totaled some sixty-four persons.
Look, you turn those into numbers, and then <fex>592 and 74</fex> total 666, right?
A modicum <fex>of seepage on the floor</fex> is to be expected.
A number <fex>of concerned citizens</fex> have raised objections.
She did n't know, <fex>rather she suspected</fex> .
As a representative in Congress in the years 1783-85, Gerry numbered <fex>among those who had possessed talent as Revolutionary agitators and wartime leaders</fex>.
Just be glad that <fex>you</fex> number among the living.
<fex>At that time</fex>, the factory numbered among the largest in the western half of North America.
<fex>In Europe</fex>, the sport counts among the economic branches of industry which generate employment among the young people.
